===Etymology===
Appears to be a compound of {{w|Classical Japanese}} {{com|ja|明る|tr1=akaru|t1=to brighten|し|tr2=shi|t2=adjectival suffix}}. This adjectival suffix forms a classical {{m|ja|ク活用|tr=ku-katsuyō|t=ku-adjective}}.

Cognates for 明る include:

* {{der|ja|ojp|明る|akar-|t=to brighten, to redden}}<ref>[https://oncoj.orinst.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/oncoj_dictionary.sh?search=L030012 Old Japanese akar] in [https://oncoj.ninjal.ac.jp/ Oxford NINJAL Corpus of Old Japanese]</ref>

* Modern forms {{m|ja|明かす|tr=akasu|t=to reveal, to pass through the night}}, {{m|ja|明ける|tr=akeru|t=to dawn}}

* {{der|ja|ojp|赤|aka|t=red}}<ref>[https://oncoj.orinst.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/oncoj_dictionary.sh?search=L007016 Old Japanese aka] in [https://oncoj.ninjal.ac.jp/ Oxford NINJAL Corpus of Old Japanese]</ref>, modern forms {{m|ja|赤|tr=aka|t=red, noun}}, {{m|ja|赤い|tr=akai|t=red, adjective}}

* {{cog|jpx-pro|*aka}}, {{cog|jpx-ryu-pro|*aka}}, {{cog|xug|赤|tr=hakā}}, {{cog|mvi|赤|tr=aka}}, {{cog|ryn|赤|tr=aka}}, {{cog|ryu|赤|tr=aka}}, also {{cog|ryu|赤さん|tr=akasan}}, {{cog|rys|赤|tr=aka}}, {{cog|yoi|赤|tr=aga}}

